Application Specifications:
a. Architecture
The system uses a three-tier architecture:
Frontend: User interface (event browsing, booking)
Backend: Handles logic (authentication, reservations)
Database: Stores users, events, and tickets
Flow: User → Frontend → Backend → Database → Response to user
 _____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Database Model
Main tables:
Users (user_id, name, email, password, role)
Events (event_id, title, location, date, capacity)
Reservations (reservation_id, user_id, event_id, ticket_number)

Relationships:
One user → many reservations
One event → many reservations

Constraints:
Email and ticket number are unique
Reservations must link to valid users and events
